<HEADLINE>
Come march in Washington DC on Saturday Jan. 27
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<POST>
<POSTER> "Timothy Golden   BandTechnology.com" &lt;tttppp...@yahoo.com&gt; </POSTER>
<POSTDATE> 2007-01-26T07:25:00 </POSTDATE>
http://www.unitedforpeace.org

There will be a huge march in DC tomorrow to oppose the Iraq war and
the philosophy of the American government. I'll be carrying an upside
down American flag and depending on how strong I'm feeling may put a
black X through the field of stars. I am disgusted with the level that
the Democrats are taking the conversation to. Where is the discussion
of a mistaken US foreign policy? We propped up the Taliban and now we
are destroying them. We propped up Saddam Hussein and have destroyed
him. The pattern only begins there and extends backward through recent
time. Al Quaida are only the first in line. Perhaps this country should
address their greivances. If their greivances are valid then I am
forced to conclude that the US is a power hungry war-monger. This is
not a power struggle with a stronger nation. It is a power struggle
against humanity. This U.S. federal government is a failure.
Nationalism is failing us. Any nationalistic country is capable of this
type of failure...

How will the US dismantle its nuclear weapons? Dismantling the US is a
clear path to achieve this end. This is a path that conservatives might
also support. One might even argue that Bush is doing the ultimate act
in abusing the federal government to this point. The US does not make
wise choices. It makes greedy choices. We stab the backs of those that
we empower and American pay-offs rule the planet. I am a party to all
of this action since I pay taxes to the government and half of that
money goes to the Pentagon. I have paid for the bullets that kill
innocent Iraqis. Numerous misdeeds which I have no knowledge of are
done in my name. I refuse to accept these misdeeds even if they are
done for me or by me, no matter how indirect the path.

A march in the Capitol may be only symbollic to you. Carrying a flag or
even burning one may be only an informational message. One day this
energy that is still building via a social delay mechanism may break
the threshold and when it does where will you stand? Come to DC and
join with the conscientious; the conscious ones. While the rest are
asleep with the waves lapping at their feet you can awaken them. We do
not believe in killing. We oppose killing, but that does not relieve
the anger that we feel when our government kills with our money. This
level of indirection needs to be exposed. A brainwashed soldier pulls
the trigger. Who is guilty? You are if you payed taxes.  You are
especially guilty if you've ever worked on any pentagon funded
projects. You are if you work for a defence contractor. You are guilty
even if you are an American citizen. A sleeping mind is a brainwashed
mind. The soldier comes home and awakens with frightful images and deep
guilt for pulling the trigger. The social flux sweeps us along like a
bit of dust. To be a good dog what has one to do? There is a strong
distinction between the passive and the pacifists.

I have spoken with enough people about the anger that they feel. It
wells up and only diminishes out of exhaustion. There is a tendency for
these angry individuals to pooh-pooh the peace crowd. I know because I
am one of them. The peace crowd will heartily welcome you angry people.
Get your anger out. Do you take the red, white, or blue pill?

"... for me, truth is the sovereign principle, which includes
numerous other principles. This truth is not only truthfulness in word,
but truthfulness in thought also, and not only the relative truth of
our conception, but the Absolute Truth, the Eternal Principle, that is
God. There are innumerable definitions of God, because His
manifestations are innumerable. They overwhelm me with wonder and awe
and for a moment stun me. But I worship God as Truth only."
- M.K. Gandhi

Beyond these words I can only say that symmetry is a balance that rules
all things. Denial of symmetry will fail. Therefore the current path of
the U.S. federal government is a dead end.
Please join us in Washington, DC.

-Tim
