As I listen to Amy Goodman's coverage of Saturday's rally
http://www.archive.org/download/dn2007-0130/dn2007-0130-1.ogg
http://www.archive.org/download/dn2007-0130/dn2007-0130-1_64kb.mp3
I am reassured that the energy that I felt at this rally is a reality.
It is a strange space to feel the social tear that we are in the midst
of.

Perelman has something with his surgeries on Ricci flows.
Perhaps he can give some advice on the surgery that is about to go on
in this country. Even in its best outcome the organs of the U.S.
federal government will spill out on the table. As we are left sorting
through them the strange beast and its ugly insides require
amputations beyond standard procedure. Who can do such surgery? Surely
it will take the world's best doctors. So we will see them file in
with second and third opinions on which organs to pull first. Their
consensus will probably be that the beast must first be anesthetized
for any such investigation to take place.

That in itself poses a huge challenge. How does one convince this
monster that it must undergo surgery? If it can only see that as it
swells like a balloon it grows easier to pop... That a tear is already
underway...

Is it too late already for the ugly thing? Do doctors still have
compassion left for it? Under some circumstances such animals are best
put down and the monster knowing this may not accept anesthetic. So we
arrive at the present state, or at least my own fantastic imagery of
it.

I carried my upside down U.S. flag all day at the rally and could
easily have filled it up with signatories had I tried. As it is the
incidental acquaintences that I made form a verification of its
symbollism. People from around the US and even further (one man from
Bolivia) freely signed my flag and left their own messages on it.
Several veterans in wheelchairs even signed on. One declared that I
should not let the flag touch the ground. I explained to him that when
people sign it I put it on the ground and that it is upside down
anyways. He calmly held his position and then proceeded to sign onto
it. That's very meaningful to me.

The election of a d.p. majority to the congress has not quelled the
peace movement. If anything it has further engaged it. A few more
exposures of the monster's internals should help to understand that
like it or not things are going to change. If the proper procedures
are not taken the impact will be worldwide. Certainly those routes
which are known perils form a primary theoretical foundation which
needs to be addressed by the doctors and prevented. Operating with
this preventive assumption firmly verified would be helpful.

Perhaps a wide UN presence in the US could be helpful to monitor the
situation. I would breath a sigh of relief to see some light blue
hats. I'm scared. One more gash from an enemy and it is going to
explode.

Vermont's youth:  You Rock !

-Tim
